  "prompt": "When and how did WWI start and end?",
  "response": "World War I, also known as the Great War, began on July 28, 1914. The immediate trigger was the assassination of Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria-Hungary on June 28, 1914, by Gavrilo Princip, a Bosnian Serb nationalist. This assassination set off a chain of events that led to Austria-Hungary declaring war on Serbia. Due to a complex web of alliances and treaties, many other countries were quickly drawn into the conflict.\n\nThe war involved major powers divided into two main alliances: the Allies, which included the United Kingdom, France, Russia, and later, the United States among others, and the Central Powers, which included Germany, Austria-Hungary, the Ottoman Empire, and Bulgaria.\n\nWorld War I ended on November 11, 1918, when an armistice was signed between the Allies and Germany, effectively ceasing hostilities. This armistice was followed by the signing of the Treaty of Versailles on June 28, 1919, which officially ended the state of war between Germany and the Allied Powers. The Treaty of Versailles imposed heavy reparations and territorial losses on Germany and aimed to prevent further conflict.",
